01:11:04,100 --> 01:11:06,200
The train had knocked Ray Brower out of his Keds...

1017
01:11:06,270 --> 01:11:09,210
just like it had knocked the life out of his body.

1018
01:11:09,280 --> 01:11:10,540
Jesus.

1019
01:11:12,610 --> 01:11:14,410
The kid wasn't sick.

1020
01:11:14,480 --> 01:11:16,240
The kid wasn't sleeping.

1021
01:11:17,450 --> 01:11:18,970
The kid was dead.

1022
01:11:34,470 --> 01:11:36,400
Let's look for some long branches.

1023
01:11:36,470 --> 01:11:38,900
We'll build him a stretcher.

1024
01:11:51,420 --> 01:11:52,410
Gordie

1025
01:12:00,990 --> 01:12:02,760
Why did you have to die?

1026
01:12:03,930 --> 01:12:06,520
- What's the matter with Gordie? - Nothing.

1027
01:12:06,600 --> 01:12:09,260
Why don't you guys just go over there and look for some branches, okay?

1028
01:12:09,340 --> 01:12:10,770
Okay.

1029
01:12:22,680 --> 01:12:25,450
Why did he have to die, Chris?

1030
01:12:25,520 --> 01:12:29,110
Why did Denny have to die? Why?

1031
01:12:31,020 --> 01:12:32,460
I don't know.

1032
01:12:34,030 --> 01:12:36,290
- It should have been me. - Don't say that.

1033
01:12:36,360 --> 01:12:39,660
- It should have been me. - Don't say that, man.

1034
01:12:40,870 --> 01:12:42,300
I'm no good.

1035
01:12:42,370 --> 01:12:44,300
My dad said it. I'm no good.

1036
01:12:44,370 --> 01:12:45,960
He doesn't know you.

1037
01:12:47,370 --> 01:12:50,970
- He hates me. - He doesn't hate you.

1038
01:12:51,040 --> 01:12:54,640
- He hates me! - No! He just doesn't know you.

1039
01:12:54,710 --> 01:12:58,310
He hates me. My dad hates me.

1040
01:12:59,390 --> 01:13:02,320
He hates me. I'm no good.

1041
01:13:25,740 --> 01:13:28,510
You're gonna be a great writer someday, Gordie.

1042
01:13:30,080 --> 01:13:34,350
You might even write about us guys, if you ever get hard up for material.

1043
01:13:52,610 --> 01:13:56,370
Guess I'd have to be pretty hard up, huh?

1044
01:13:58,110 --> 01:13:59,540
Yeah.

1045
01:14:02,620 --> 01:14:04,410
What the fuck do you know about this?

1046
01:14:05,780 --> 01:14:09,050
Son of a bitch! My little brother.

1047
01:14:10,990 --> 01:14:14,480
You wasn't planning on taking the body from us, was you, boys?

1048
01:14:16,630 --> 01:14:19,790
You get away, man. We found him. We got dibs.

1049
01:14:21,300 --> 01:14:24,270
We better start running, Eyeball. They got dibs.

1050
01:14:24,340 --> 01:14:26,400
We earned him, man. You guys came in a car.

1051
01:14:26,470 --> 01:14:28,170
That's not fair. He's ours.

1052
01:14:28,570 --> 01:14:30,840
That's not fair. He's ours.

1053
01:14:30,910 --> 01:14:32,170
Well, not anymore.

1054
01:14:32,240 --> 01:14:34,080
There's four of us, Eyeball.

1055
01:14:34,150 --> 01:14:35,670
You just make your move.

1056
01:14:35,750 --> 01:14:37,980
Oh, we will. Don't you worry.

1057
01:14:42,550 --> 01:14:45,460
Vern, you little son of a whore.

1058
01:14:45,520 --> 01:14:46,750
You was under the porch!

1059
01:14:46,830 --> 01:14:48,920
No, I swear! It wasn't me!

1060
01:14:48,990 --> 01:14:50,590
You little keyhole-peeping bung.

1061
01:14:50,660 --> 01:14:52,790
I ought to beat the living shit out of you.

1062
01:14:59,510 --> 01:15:01,440
You guys have two choices.

1063
01:15:02,510 --> 01:15:05,270
You either leave quietly, and we take the body...

1064
01:15:05,340 --> 01:15:08,210
or you stay and we beat the shit out of you...

1065
01:15:09,010 --> 01:15:10,450
and we take the body.

1066
01:15:10,520 --> 01:15:12,280
Besides, me and Billy found him first.

1067
01:15:12,350 --> 01:15:14,290
Yeah, Vern told us how you found him.

1068
01:15:14,350 --> 01:15:17,950
Oh, Billy! I wish we never boosted that car!

1069
01:15:18,020 --> 01:15:21,980
Oh, Billy, I think I just turned my Fruit of the Looms into a fudge factory.

1070
01:15:22,060 --> 01:15:24,550
- That's it. Your ass is grass. - Hold it.

1071
01:15:28,200 --> 01:15:30,000
Okay, Chambers, you little faggot.

1072
01:15:30,070 --> 01:15:32,300
This is your last chance.

1073
01:15:33,210 --> 01:15:34,640
What do you say, kid?

1074
01:15:36,380 --> 01:15:39,210
Why don't you go home and fuck your mother some more?

1075
01:15:44,050 --> 01:15:45,480
You're dead.

1076
01:15:46,220 --> 01:15:47,740
Come on, Chris. Let's split.

1077
01:15:48,550 --> 01:15:50,550
- They're not taking him. - Man, this is crazy.

1078
01:15:50,620 --> 01:15:53,390
- They're not taking him. - He's got a knife, man!

1079
01:15:54,390 --> 01:15:56,020
Ace, come on, man.

1080
01:16:00,730 --> 01:16:02,430
You're gonna have to kill me, Ace.

1081
01:16:02,500 --> 01:16:04,160
No problem.

1082
01:16:18,080 --> 01:16:19,680
You're not taking him.

1083
01:16:19,750 --> 01:16:21,580
Nobody's taking him.

1084
01:16:23,420 --> 01:16:27,450
Come on, kid,just give me the gun before you take your foot off.

1085
01:16:28,430 --> 01:16:31,260
You ain't got the sack to shoot a woodchuck.

1086
01:16:32,430 --> 01:16:34,960
Don't move, Ace.

1087
01:16:35,770 --> 01:16:38,430
I'll kill you. I swear to God.

1088
01:16:40,110 --> 01:16:42,300
Come on, Lachance, give me the gun.

1089
01:16:44,780 --> 01:16:47,470
You must have at least some of your brother's good sense.

1090
01:16:52,120 --> 01:16:54,050
Suck my fat one...

1091
01:16:54,120 --> 01:16:57,490
you cheap, dime-store hood.

1092
01:17:03,460 --> 01:17:05,090
What are you gonna do, shoot us all?

1093
01:17:06,130 --> 01:17:07,560
No, Ace.

1094
01:17:07,630 --> 01:17:09,290
Just you.

1095
01:17:19,140 --> 01:17:21,010
We're gonna get you for this.

1096
01:17:21,650 --> 01:17:23,580
Maybe you will, and maybe you won't.

1097
01:17:24,480 --> 01:17:25,920
Oh, we will.

1098
01:17:38,500 --> 01:17:41,630
We're not gonna forget this, if that's what you're thinking.

1099
01:17:42,840 --> 01:17:44,860
This is big time, baby.

1100
01:18:01,520 --> 01:18:03,320
''Suck my fat one''?

1101
01:18:04,390 --> 01:18:07,050
Whoever told you you had a fat one, Lachance?

1102
01:18:08,860 --> 01:18:11,350
Biggest one in four counties.

1103
01:18:12,030 --> 01:18:13,460
Yeah.

1104
01:18:29,210 --> 01:18:30,740
Are we gonna take him?

1105
01:18:31,280 --> 01:18:32,410
No

1106
01:18:34,050 --> 01:18:38,390
But we came all this way. We were supposed to be heroes.

1107
01:18:40,560 --> 01:18:42,650
Not this way, Teddy.

1108
01:18:45,900 --> 01:18:48,530
Chris, give me a hand.

1109
01:18:50,400 --> 01:18:52,340
Ray Brower's body was found...

1110
01:18:52,400 --> 01:18:55,840
but neither our gang nor their gang got the credit.

1111
01:18:55,910 --> 01:18:58,340
In the end, we decided that an anonymous phone call...

1112
01:18:58,410 --> 01:19:00,840
was the best thing to do.

1113
01:19:06,420 --> 01:19:07,850
We headed home.

1114
01:19:07,920 --> 01:19:10,860
And although many thoughts raced through our minds...

1115
01:19:10,920 --> 01:19:12,360
we barely spoke.

1116
01:19:16,600 --> 01:19:19,190
We walked through the night and made it back to Castle Rock...

1117
01:19:19,260 --> 01:19:23,700
a little past 5:00 on Sunday morning, the day before Labor Day.

1118
01:19:25,440 --> 01:19:27,530
We'd only been gone two days...

1119
01:19:27,610 --> 01:19:30,040
but somehow the town seemed different...

1120
01:19:30,110 --> 01:19:31,540
smaller.

1121
01:19:48,790 --> 01:19:51,390
Well, see you in school.

1122
01:19:52,460 --> 01:19:54,060
Yeah.

1123
01:19:55,570 --> 01:19:57,730
See you in junior high.

1124
01:20:11,480 --> 01:20:12,810
Penny!

1125
01:20:21,490 --> 01:20:25,760
I better get home before my mom puts me on the ten-most-wanted list.

1126
01:20:34,010 --> 01:20:36,300
Hey, Chris.

1127
01:20:36,380 --> 01:20:38,280
No hard feelings, okay?

1128
01:20:39,180 --> 01:20:40,970
No way, man.

1129
01:20:45,020 --> 01:20:49,280
Have gun will travel reads the card of a man

1130
01:20:49,350 --> 01:20:54,310
A knight without armor in a savage land

1131
01:20:54,390 --> 01:20:56,620
His fast gun for hire

1132
01:21:05,040 --> 01:21:08,630
As time went on, we saw less and less of Teddy and Vern...

1133
01:21:08,710 --> 01:21:12,640
until eventually they became just two more faces in the halls.

1134
01:21:12,710 --> 01:21:14,470
It happens sometimes.

1135
01:21:14,550 --> 01:21:17,710
Friends come in and out of your life like busboys in a restaurant.

1136
01:21:18,880 --> 01:21:21,320
I heard that Vern got married out of high school...

1137
01:21:21,390 --> 01:21:25,980
had four kids and is now the forklift operator at the Arsenault Lumber Yard.

1138
01:21:26,060 --> 01:21:28,320
Teddy tried several times to get into the army...

1139
01:21:28,390 --> 01:21:31,160
but his eyes and his ear kept him out.

1140
01:21:31,230 --> 01:21:33,320
Last I'd heard, he'd spent some time in jail...

1141
01:21:33,400 --> 01:21:36,160
and was now doing odd jobs around Castle Rock.

1142
01:21:44,580 --> 01:21:47,550
I'm never gonna get out of this town, am I, Gordie?

1143
01:21:49,410 --> 01:21:51,910
You can do anything you want, man.

1144
01:21:52,920 --> 01:21:54,680
Yeah.

1145
01:21:54,750 --> 01:21:56,190
Sure.

1146
01:22:04,260 --> 01:22:05,920
Gimme some skin.

1147
01:22:14,940 --> 01:22:16,270
I'll see you.

1148
01:22:16,340 --> 01:22:18,370
Not if I see you first.

1149
01:22:23,120 --> 01:22:24,450
Chris did get out.

1150
01:22:24,520 --> 01:22:27,210
He enrolled in the college courses with me...

1151
01:22:27,290 --> 01:22:30,880
and although it was hard, he gutted it out, like he always did.

1152
01:22:30,960 --> 01:22:33,950
He went on to college, and eventually became a lawyer.

1153
01:22:34,860 --> 01:22:37,730
Last week he entered a fast-food restaurant.

1154
01:22:37,800 --> 01:22:40,730
Just ahead of him, two men got into an argument.

1155
01:22:40,800 --> 01:22:42,730
One of them pulled a knife.

1156
01:22:42,800 --> 01:22:45,740
Chris, who had always made the best peace, tried to break it up.

1157
01:22:46,970 --> 01:22:48,910
He was stabbed in the throat.

1158
01:22:48,970 --> 01:22:50,910
He died almost instantly.

1159
01:23:10,830 --> 01:23:13,260
Dad, can we go now?

1160
01:23:13,330 --> 01:23:16,770
- You ready? - Yeah. We've been ready for an hour.

1161
01:23:20,170 --> 01:23:21,940
Okay, I'll be right there.

1162
01:23:22,010 --> 01:23:23,600
He said that a half hour ago.

1163
01:23:23,680 --> 01:23:26,940
Yeah. My dad's weird. He gets like that when he's writing.

